data.description: Take a look at this special and unique property in the heart of Carson City. Sitting just below the Kings Canyon waterfall, this charming duplex overlooks the city.  One unit is a studio which is rented until September, 2024.  The other is a one-bedroom unit which is rented on a month-to-month lease.  The entire parcel is 1.67 acres with natural landscaping.  Utilities are propane, spring-fed well, electricity, and septic.  Tenants pay for electricity and propane. Owner pays for storm drain utility and trash service.  This property is a great investment property or buyers could live in one side and rent the other.  Don't miss out on this amazing one-of-kind property with so much land situated in the Sierra foothills! Property is also currently zoned for horses. Please ask listing agent for escrow information as escrow is already open.
